records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which amends count 1 to misdemenaor possess cocaine, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(c) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
GUILTY Plea entered to the amended charge in count 1.  Convicted.
GULTY plea entered to the charge of felony bail jumping in count 2.  Convicted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) submit to random drug screens and pay for same;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) no contact with Avelardo Vazquez;
6) pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court orders the defendant to undergo a cocaine assessment.
The Court authorizes that the weapon be destroyed after the co-defendant's cases are closed.
The count 2, felony bail jumping, the Court orders expungement under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.
Minutes.
